The Authority may, for any reason consistent with the purposes of this Act and the public interest, approve, refuse or restrict the carrying on by the licensee of any of the following activities -
* a merger or a major acquisition or sale of its assets or securities;
<\li1>

A generation licensee shall comply with the following conditions, to -
* subject to subsection (4), submit to the Authority, for review and approval, the rates, terms and conditions for any power sales contract it has with any other licensee;
* submit to the Authority, the technical, safety and interconnection standards for the proposed generation facility;
* if connected at a grid receiving point, make the licensed generation facilities available to the dispatch licensee at the receiving point for the safe, reliable, non-discriminatory and economic dispatch and operation of the transmission grid and connected facilities, pursuant to the terms of its power sales contract or its approved rates and terms and conditions of service;
* if connected at a distribution receiving point, make the licensed generation facilities available to the distribution licensee at the receiving point for safe, reliable, non-discriminatory and economic dispatch to supply the distribution licenseeâ¢s load, pursuant to the terms of its power sales contract or its approved rates and terms and conditions of service;
* comply with all applicable requirements regarding the co-ordination of the operation of generation facilities with the transmission grid and distribution facilities, including reasonable instructions issued by the dispatch licensee or distribution licensee, as applicable; and
* comply with all other terms and conditions of the licence.
* intends solely to export electricity from The Gambia; or

A transmission licensee shall comply with the following conditions, to •
* develop and maintain the transmission grid in a manner adequate to support the needs of generation licensees, dispatch licen-sees, distribution licensees and direct customers within The Gambia;
